com.raweng.built

Class BuiltUser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.raweng.built.BuiltObject
      • com.raweng.built.BuiltUser

  • public class BuiltUser
extends BuiltObject
    This class allows registering user for an application and other features such as logging in and logging out.
    After the log in, the getAuthToken() will be given in response. This getAuthToken() is to be supplied for subsequent requests if the the request is to be identified as being from that user.
    Author:
    built.io. Inc

      • login

        public void login(java.lang.String email,
                  java.lang.String password,
                  com.raweng.built.BuiltResultCallBack callback)
        Login BuiltUser by providing email as ID and sign-up password.
        Parameters:
        email - email.
        password - password.
        callback - BuiltResultCallBack object to notify the application when the request has completed.

        Note:

      • You can access application user data by accessing getAuthToken(), getUserUid(), getFirstName(), getLastName(), getUserName(), getEmailId()
      • You must call createInstallation from BuiltInstallation class after this method.


        • Example :
          // 'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
 BuiltUser userObject = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b").user();

 userObject.login("something@email", "password", new BuiltResultCallBack() {

      @Override
      public void onCompletion(BuiltResponseType responseType, BuiltError builtError) {

      }
 });

      • fetchUserUidForEmail

        public void fetchUserUidForEmail(java.lang.String emailId,
                                 com.raweng.built.BuiltUserResultCallback callback)
        Fetches the user's uid based on email address
        Parameters:
        emailId - email id.
        callback - BuiltUserResultCallback object to notify the application when the request has completed.

        Note :

      • This call will allow you to retrieve the uid for an user, whether or not the user exists. A means for identifying the user needs to be provided. This comes in handy, for example, when you need to apply ACL for an user that may not exist in the system at the moment.


        • Example :
         // 'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
 BuiltUser userObject = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b").user();

 userObject.fetchUserUidForEmail("something@email.com", new BuiltUserResultCallback() {

      @Override
      public void onCompletion(BuiltResponseType responseType, String userUid, BuiltError builtError) {

      }
 });

      • on

        public void on(Built.EventType eventType,
               com.raweng.built.BuiltOnEventCallback callback)
        This function registers an event listener.

        [Only avaliable with realtime]
        Overrides:
        on in class BuiltObject
        Parameters:
        eventType - event name.
        callback - BuiltOnEventCallback object to notify the application when the request has completed.

        Given below is the list of supported events.

        Create [Work with BuiltApplication.user()]:- The 'create' event is triggered when a new user is created in the class with which the Object constructor is associated. Registered callback is invoked with the created object.

        Update :- Update event is triggered when any/uid_specific object in the class with which the Object constructor is associated is modified. Registered callback is invoked with the updated object.

        Delete :- Delete event is triggered when any/uid_specific object in the class with which the Object constructor is associated is deleted. Registered callback is invoked with the deleted object.

        Broadcast :- Broadcast event is triggered when a message is broadcast for all objects belonging to a particular class. Registered callback is invoked with the broadcast message.



        Example :
         //'blt5dsamplef62a111a' is dummy uid of an application.
 BuiltApplication builtApplication = Built.application(context, "blt5dsamplef62a111a");
 BuiltUser person = builtApplication.user();
 person.on(Built.EventType.CREATE, new BuiltOnEventCallback() {
        
      @Override
      public void onReceive(Object object, BuiltError error) {
        

      }
 });
